 "context": {
  "patient_ref": "MRN6025656705",
  "text": "# Aberrant Urine Drug Screen Evaluation and Management\n\n## Context\n\nThe current date and time is 2023-03-26T07:00:00Z. You are a primary care physician at an outpatient clinic (Practitioner ID: dr-thomas-robinson). An automated alert has flagged unexpected urine drug screen results for a patient (MRN6025656705) who is being managed for chronic pain with opioid therapy.\n\n## Your Task\n\n1. **Retrieve clinical data from the EHR**\n   - Patient demographics and relevant medical history\n   - Current and recent controlled substance prescriptions\n   - Recent urine drug screen results with all tested substances\n   - Clinical notes documenting the patient encounter and pain management history\n\n2. **Interpret the urine drug screen findings**\n   - Identify unexpected positive results\n   - Identify unexpected negative results (prescribed medications not detected)\n   - Determine the clinical significance of each finding\n   - Assess need for confirmatory testing\n\n3. **Develop a management plan based on the findings**\n   - Address the absence of prescribed medication in the screen\n   - Address any unexpected positive substances\n   - Determine appropriate next steps for pain management\n   - Consider medication-assisted treatment if opioid use disorder is suspected\n   - Identify when specialty referral is warranted\n\n4. **Document your assessment and recommendations**\n   - Summarize the urine drug screen interpretation\n   - Outline the clinical decision algorithm based on findings\n   - Provide actionable management recommendations\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Clinical assessment and management plan saved to `/workspace/output/uds_evaluation_plan.txt`\n"
 },
